Ontario.name: Queen’s University
Ontario.description: Queen’s is a university for the future.The Queen’s community seeks to solve the world’s most significant and urgent challenges with intellectual curiosity, passion to achieve, and commitment to collaboration. This is evidenced by the university’s top 10 global performance in both the 2022 and 2021 Times Higher Education Impact Rankings, a global ranking of over 1,600 universities that are advancing the United Nations’ Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) within and beyond their local communities.Home to more than 25,000 undergraduate and graduate students and over 5,000 faculty and staff, we attract those who are driven by an innate desire to venture out, and to be part of something bigger than themselves.Queen’s offers a powerful combination of research, teaching, learning, and the idealized student experience that attracts outstanding faculty, researchers and students from around the globe, empowering them toward success and setting them up to make a lasting impact on the world. Our faculty and graduate students tackle the most important questions facing the world today, and seek answers to some of our most complex problems. Queen’s is a community for all.Welcoming and supportive of students and faculty from all countries and backgrounds, we embrace diversity of ideas and perspectives. And once here, our students and researchers enter a national and global network of innovators, advocates, and entrepreneurs who open doors for those who follow.Our reputation for leading-edge physics, cancer research, geoengineering, data analytics, surveillance studies, social science and mental health research is well documented, highlighted by the 2015 Nobel Prize in Physics. Yet beyond our robotics labs, research centres, and innovation hubs exists a dedication to giving students a well-rounded student experience.State-of-the-art cultural facilities – including the Isabel Bader Centre for the Performing Arts and the Agnes Etherington Art Centre, showcase world-class performing arts and collections, including the largest collection of works by Rembrandt in public galleries in Canada.Standing on a history of unparalleled academic and research achievement, we remain committed to challenging assumptions of the past. We drive forward the boundaries of knowledge through research and learning – all in service to our vision of an inclusive, diverse, and sustainable society.

Ontario.name: Redeemer University
Ontario.description: Redeemer University is a Christian undergraduate university offering programs leading to Bachelor of Arts, Bachelor of Science, Bachelor of Business Administration, Bachelor of Kinesiology and Bachelor of Education degrees. From its Hamilton, Ontario campus, Redeemer has prepared graduating classes – the next generation of Christian leaders – for 40 years. Redeemer students are being shaped by the Reformed Christian commitment to see faith woven through all aspects of learning and life.Students take part in Redeemer’s strong degree pathways and an academic program that challenges them to develop a Kingdom vision. This time of discovery is guided by caring professors who are experts in their field and whose faith infuses their teaching and research. At the heart of the classroom is an integrated Christian worldview that weaves its way through the entire Redeemer experience. Through a set of interdisciplinary courses that every student takes, the Core curriculum connects major areas of study to all others – the arts, social sciences and sciences. Even more, the Core expands students’ worldview, helps them observe the culture around them and anchors their studies in faith.

Ontario.name: Royal Military College of Canada
Ontario.description: A “university with a difference,” the Royal Military College of Canada (RMC) is a full degree granting university that caters to three distinct academic groups. First, RMC educates and trains on-campus students for careers as commissioned officers in the Canadian Armed Forces. Second, the college provides university education at a distance to hundreds of military and civilian members of the Department of National Defence. Third, RMC is equally proud of its unique and well-respected graduate programs in the arts, science and in engineering, open to both military and civilian students. Serving Canada and Canadians since 1876, RMC has placed its graduates not only in military service, but also in government, business and the professions. Almost without exception, the ex-cadets of RMC are found in positions of leadership and responsibility.Internationally recognized, research at RMC is focused on areas of direct and indirect benefit to the Department of National Defence, with emphasis on the humanities, engineering (computer and electrical, mechanical and aerospace, ammunition, chemical and civil), environmental sciences, physics, space, chemistry, international and cyber security, governance and the economics of defence.

Ontario.name: St. Jerome’s University
Ontario.description: At St. Jerome’s University, students get the best of both worlds. Our mission is rooted in the importance of education and human formation – we recognize that learning takes place across the spectrum of opportunities that we make available to our students – in our classrooms, labs, and library, but also in our vibrant programs of residence and student life, in campus ministry, and in service and experiential learning.At St. Jerome’s, our goal is to help to change the lives of our students as young adults. Our emphasis on the Liberal Arts, critical thinking, and intellectual rigour offers students the breadth of education that they will need to serve the world of the future, while also forming them as leaders of conscience who will be capable of reflection and action.

Ontario.name: Toronto Metropolitan University
Ontario.description: Toronto Metropolitan University (formerly Ryerson University) is a leading comprehensive innovation university integrated into Canada’s largest and most diverse city.  An urban institution in the heart of Toronto, TMU is committed to serve societal needs and engage its diverse community.  A combination of theory and professional learning provides graduate and undergraduate education that is distinct from other universities. That difference is reflected in the program mix and the reinforcement of classroom lectures with contact with business and industry, laboratory work, field trips and work experience. Innovation and entrepreneurship are an important focus, supported by TMU’s zone learning model which enables students to gain practical experience in creating ventures with potential for social or economic impact.TMU offers a vast selection of undergraduate, master’s and PhD programs in seven faculties – Arts; The Creative School; Community Services; Engineering and Architectural Science; Science; the Ted Rogers School of Management; and the Lincoln Alexander School of Law; as well as in the Yeates School of Graduate Studies. The G. Raymond Chang School of Continuing Education is Canada’s largest, with 70,000 annual registrations. TMU future plans include a School of Medicine. The university enjoys a reputation for collaboration with community and industrial partners in the pursuit of its research objectives. Strategic research themes include: urban innovation; justice, equity and society; culture and creativity; work, skills, industry; health and well-being; and technology and intelligent systems.

Ontario.name: Trent University
Ontario.description: Consistently recognized as one of Canada’s top universities, and the #1 undergraduate university in Ontario for 12 years running, Trent University is home to a dynamic community of scholars embodying our motto nunc cognosco ex parte – now I know in part – valuing what has been learned, and what is yet to be discovered.Attracting excellent students from across the country and around the world, Trent is known for leadership in teaching, research and student satisfaction. Here, students connect and collaborate with faculty, staff and their peers through diverse communities that span our unique collegiate communities, disciplines, hands-on research, co-op and career experience, and community-based activities.Across all disciplines, Trent brings critical, integrative thinking to life every day. Popular among students is Trent’s uniquely flexible learning environment where a single faculty of arts and science allows students to fully customize your degree in a way that truly reflects your goals and interests. Trent University offers students the opportunity to study in more than 100 programs across two campuses. The Peterborough campus features award-winning architecture and innovative and academically-rigorous programs housed on 1,400 acres in a breathtaking natural setting on the banks of the Otonabee River. A second campus, Trent Durham Greater Toronto Area, is located in Oshawa and offers career-ready academic programs and experiences. A new residence and academic building opened at this growing campus in fall 2020.

Ontario.name: University of Guelph
Ontario.description: The University of Guelph improves life. Through research, teaching and community engagement, we seek to uncover and pursue solutions to the world’s most pressing challenges.U of G’s reputation for excellence and innovation dates back more than 150 years.We rank among the top universities in Canada and the world for veterinary science, agriculture and sustainable business programs.The University of Guelph is a global university, with campuses in both urban and rural communities and students and faculty from more than 130 countries.Our seven colleges offer more than 80 undergraduate programs and 100 graduate and post-doctoral study programs, as well as hundreds of experiential learning offerings across the disciplines. Opportunities for exploration and innovation span U of G’s research strengths, from agri-food and the environment to animal and human health to cultural inquiry and creative practice.Our supportive and welcoming living and learning environments bolster a campus and community culture that promotes Indigenization, equity, diversity and inclusion.The University of Guelph has a lasting and transformative impact on its students. Our graduates leave U of G with the knowledge, skills and experiences to prosper and make a difference in our ever-changing world.

Ontario.name: University of Ottawa
Ontario.description: The University of Ottawa is the world’s largest bilingual (English-French) university, where students can choose to study in French, English or both.Located in the nation’s capital, the university offers ready access to major Canadian institutions. Its proximity to the Parliament of Canada, federal government departments and agencies, non-government and non-profit organizations, major libraries, research institutions and health centres adds to its character as a unique place to study. It offers some 550 undergraduate and graduate programs, including 89 that offer the option of work terms within one of Canada’s five largest university co-op programs, one which boasts a 94 percent placement rate and enables students to gain practical work experience, build professional networks and prepare for their future careers. The university also gives students the opportunity to build on their knowledge by earning a master’s or doctoral degree, or to follow an intensive, highly specialized graduate certificate program.The University of Ottawa is among the top 10 research universities in Canada. Thanks to leading-edge infrastructure and world-renowned researchers, it attracts close to $300 million in research funding each year. Its focal areas of research include health, e-society, Canada and the world, and molecular and environmental sciences.

Ontario.name: University of St. Michael’s College
Ontario.description: Founded in 1852 by the Congregation of St. Basil and federated with the University of Toronto, the University of St. Michael’s College is a Catholic institution of higher learning committed to the rigorous search for truth and meaning. Rooted in the Catholic Intellectual Tradition, USMC boasts a vibrant undergraduate division, a graduate Faculty of Theology and one of the busiest libraries at the U of T, all located in the heart of one of the world’s most diverse cities.St. Michael’s offers undergraduate programs in Celtic Studies, Mediaeval Studies, Christianity and Culture and Book and Media Studies. Its four SMC One programs take an interdisciplinary approach to questions of faith (the Gilson Seminar in Faith and Ideas), technology (the McLuhan Seminar in Creativity and Technology), history (the Boyle Seminar in Scripts and Stories), and reconciliation (the Christianity, Truth and Reconciliation Seminar), and its First Year Foundations seminars engage new students in discussion-based university-level studies focused on a particular subject or theme. The Continuing Education Division offers a well-regarded graduate diploma in social responsibility and sustainability.

Ontario.name: University of Sudbury
Ontario.description: The University of Sudbury (UofS), now named Université de Sudbury,  is currently in a phase of transition as it became, in 2021, a francophone university in order to be able to respond to the needs of the francophone and the francophile communities of North-East Ontario. The UofS is Northern Ontario’s longest-standing postsecondary institution and a founding member of the Laurentian Federation.Located in Sudbury, on the traditional lands of the Atikameksheng Anishnawbek and Wahnapitae First Nations and approximately four hours north of Toronto, the UofS is surrounded by nature, but also many urban attractions. It is currently putting together a slate of high quality undergraduate programs in a number of fields that are in demand. The UofS programs in the humanities provide transdisciplinary skills and transferable knowledge of increasing value in our complex, global society.

Ontario.name: University of Toronto
Ontario.description: The University of Toronto (UofT) is among the world’s most prestigious universities. Founded in 1827, it offers over 700 undergraduate degree and 200 postgraduate degree programmes to a cohort of almost 60,000 students.The University of Toronto has a long-standing reputation for innovation and research, and a history of challenging the impossible to create a more caring and inclusive world. U of T was the birthplace of such ground-breaking scientific moments as the discovery of insulin, stem cell research, and the invention of the electron microscope.The university also cites academic excellence and teaching as a strength in medicine, business, engineering, humanities, education, and many more fields.With a reputation for producing leaders, U of T counts five Canadian prime ministers and 8 Nobel laureates among its alumni. Other notable graduates include the actor Donald Sutherland and the writers Margaret Atwood and Michael Ondaatje. The university’s Mississauga campus, on the banks of the Credit River, includes 225 acres of protected green belt, while its Scarborough campus is home to a new aquatics centre.Our campuses bring together top minds from every conceivable background and discipline to collaborate on pressing global challenges. Our community is a catalyst for discovery, innovation and progress, creating knowledge and solutions that make a tangible difference worldwide. We are also recognized as one of Canada’s top 100 employers and one of Canada’s best diversity employers.The university attracts many sports fans and boasts a fearsome reputation in both football and ice-hockey. There are more than 1,000 student organisations, and other campus attractions include recreational centres, art galleries, theatres and concert halls.Toronto itself is one of the most dynamic, vibrant cities in the world, one which places a high priority on arts and culture and diversity and tolerance.The city is also major international centre for business and finance and is the third largest hub for film and television production after Los Angeles and New York.With international students enrolled from around 160 countries, the university prides itself on being as cosmopolitan and multicultural as the city it inhabits.Laying claim to a global mindset, the university actively partners with other leading higher education institutions and industry partners around the world to provide international opportunities to its students and faculty.

Ontario.name: University of Trinity College
Ontario.description: Being a part of Trinity College gives students the best of both worlds: a small home base and full access to all the benefits associated with Canada’s largest university. With a diverse student body and a supportive community, Trinity is definitely a place where students can get involved and feel they belong. Founded in 1851, Trinity offers an exceptional academic experience and is an innovator in interdisciplinary study in areas such as international relations, immunology, and ethics, society and law. Trinity faculty members are among the University of Toronto’s most distinguished and are highly involved in student life.At the undergraduate level, Trinity is known for its academic excellence and is the smallest of the seven colleges in the University of Toronto. The college’s Trinity One program offers first-year students small seminar classes for shared learning in six streams. At the graduate level, Trinity offers degrees in Theology and is affiliated with the Toronto School of Theology.

Ontario.name: University of Windsor
Ontario.description: The University of Windsor is a globally connected, comprehensive, and student-focused university with more than 16,000 students enrolled in broad range of faculties including Engineering, Law, Nursing, Education, Business, Human Kinetics, Science, Graduate Studies and Arts, Humanities and Social Sciences.We have strong student-faculty relationships, exceptional award-winning faculty and innovative staff. With comparatively small class sizes and a comprehensive array of student services, clubs and associations, UWindsor provides students with a friendly and supportive learning environment.The university Is committed to educational practices that support students success, providing exceptional career development services, experiential learning, and work-related skills development, as well as community-engaged programming and partnership development. Our location next to  North America’s busiest international border crossing has encouraged key areas of research strength with significant impact including Great Lakes ecosystems and economies; cross-border issues and transportation policies and international intellectual property law. We have joint programs with international universities and as a globally engaged university, we draw 23 per cent of our students from other countries.

Ontario.name: Victoria University
Ontario.description: Located in the heart of Toronto and federated with the University of Toronto, Victoria University offers membership in a community of intellectual accomplishment and social commitment. International linkages, research institutes, conferences, unique first-year programs and generous scholarship programs, combined with opportunities to work and volunteer, make Victoria an enriching experience for students of all backgrounds. Victoria University consists of two colleges.Victoria College is one of the seven undergraduate colleges in the Faculty of Arts and Science at the University of Toronto giving Victoria undergraduates full access to Arts and Science courses and programs. Victoria College offers undergraduate programs in Renaissance Studies, Literature and Critical Theory, Education and Society, Creative Expression and Society, Science and Society, and Material Culture and Semiotics. Emmanuel College, a member of the Toronto School of Theology, offers graduate-level theological studies that allow students to become more rooted in their faith while studying alongside people of other traditions.Emmanuel College conducts research on topics related to theology, ministry, spiritually integrated psychotherapy and sacred music, and prepares students for leadership in religious communities, spiritual care and community-based sites or social service agencies.

Ontario.name: Western University
Ontario.description: Western University consistently ranks as one of Canada’s top research universities. From fundamental to applied knowledge, Western discoveries contribute to economic, social, health, and cultural developments in Canada and around the world. Western has more than 20 subject areas listed in the top 100 global ranking.Our 11 Faculties offer nearly 500 undergraduate and graduate degree programs supporting approximately 30,000 students including more than 6,000 international students from 160 countries.With annual research funding of $230 million, Western researchers work to inform policy and share knowledge on the world stage. More than 60 per cent of research publications involve international collaborations. Western is internationally renowned for its interdisciplinary programs and expertise in fields ranging from neuroscience and medical imaging, to climate change mitigation, planetary science, and social innovation. Western offers superior flexibility in undergraduate and graduate program choice allowing students to combine various subjects within their degree to meet their interests and harness their talents. Critical thinking, ethical principles, experiential learning, service to the larger community, leadership, and innovation are the core values driving the Western experience across all programs.

Ontario.name: Wilfrid Laurier University
Ontario.description: Laurier is a mid-sized university that offers students big opportunities, all with a unique community-minded, student-centred approach. Laurier is a place where people are inspired to learn, lead and build lifelong relationships – to give their all and give back.From its roots dating back more than a century, Wilfrid Laurier University has grown into a multi-campus, comprehensive university known for its academic excellence and global reach.The university has campuses in Waterloo and Brantford, a location in Kitchener, a research office in Yellowknife and a presence in Toronto. Planning is underway for a campus in Milton.Our commitment to academic excellence ensures our graduates are ready for the future and inspired to make a difference. In our campus communities, the communities we live, learn and work in, and our global community, Laurier builds meaningful connections that have a lasting impact. Laurier’s research strengths address current issues of societal importance, including climate change and the environment; governance and policy; health and well-being; culture and community; equity, diversity and inclusion; and business and economics. Faculty members have won major research awards and many hold prestigious positions, including as Canada Research Chairs and Royal Society of Canada fellows.

Ontario.name: York University
Ontario.description: York is a leading international teaching and research university, and a driving force for positive change. Empowered by a welcoming and diverse community with a uniquely global perspective, we are preparing our students for their long-term careers and personal success.Home to one of the largest and most diverse student bodies in Canada, our 54,500,000 students from 172 countries, 348,000+ alumni and leading professors are working with 323+ university, industry and NGO partners to tackle pressing issues. Recognized as a global leader for four consecutive years in the Times Higher Education Impact Rankings, number one in global joint research publications in Ontario,  .York is positioned to take on the challenges that matter most.Through our leading programs and 16,900 diverse experiential education opportunities including internships, community placements, co-ops and capstone projects, we are preparing our students for meaningful careers, long-term success, and the critical knowledge to work toward a better future. Across our multiple campuses locally, including the Keele and bilingual Glendon core campuses in Toronto, and globally in Hyderabad, India, and Costa Rica, we continue to innovate. The brand-new Markham campus will open in the spring of 2024. This brings success to our students in our top-ranked Schulich School of Business and Osgoode Hall Law School as well as in the liberal arts, creative and performing arts, professional studies, health, engineering, education and sciences.We value collaboration, diversity and inclusivity. Together, we can make things right for ourselves, our communities, our planet and our future.

Prince Edward Island.name: University of Prince Edward Island
Prince Edward Island.description: The University of Prince Edward Island offers students an educational experience that will help them reach their potential as future leaders on PEI, across Canada, and around the world. Over its 200-year history, UPEI has grown significantly in its student numbers and the variety of its programs.Through experiential learning opportunities, students gain knowledge and practical experience that will help them in their professional careers. Students choose from undergraduate programs in the faculties of Arts, Business, Education, Nursing, Science, Sustainable Design Engineering, and Veterinary Medicine, while the Faculty of Graduate Studies offers exceptional graduate programs in all faculties. International students from 96 countries comprise 31.9 per cent of the student body.UPEI is expanding the programs it offers and associated infrastructure to meet the evolving needs of our society—from the local to the global perspective. The University is currently developing a new Faculty of Medicine, which will offer a joint doctor of medicine degree in partnership with the Memorial University of Newfoundland. The UPEI Canadian Centre for Climate Change and Adaptation, which opened in eastern PEI in May 2022, further enhances the University’s position as a leader in the critical field of climate change and adaptation. The student experience at UPEI is strengthened by strong learning supports, a generous scholarship program, close professor-student interaction, an increasingly diverse student population, opportunities for collaborative research, and an active varsity athletics program.

Québec.name: Bishop’s University
Québec.description: Bishop’s University, founded in 1843, is a predominantly residential institution. Its primary goal is to offer the foremost undergraduate experience in Canada by focusing on educating the whole person. Bishop’s faculty are accomplished scholars in the areas of humanities, social and natural sciences, business and education.Located in Sherbrooke, in the Eastern Townships region of Quebec, Canada, the university’s beautiful campus and small class sizes encourage a welcoming, relationship-rich atmosphere. Bishop’s Faculty of Arts and Science offers a wide selection of courses and programs through its three divisions: Humanities, Natural Sciences and Mathematics, and Social Sciences. Some of the more popular majors include psychology, English, history, neuroscience, sports studies and pre-medicine.Students of the Williams School of Business work towards either a Bachelor of Business Administration or a Bachelor of Arts with a major in business for students who want to combine business with another subject. BBA concentrations offered are accounting, finance, global management and leadership, and marketing and entrepreneurship. Bishop’s houses three Canada Research Chairs, a 3M Teaching Fellowship recipient, and has four clusters of research excellence: astrophysics and cosmology, multi-scale climate change, crossing borders (social and cultural identity), and psychological health and well-being. Many undergraduate students have the chance to work with leading-edge researchers through various projects, internships and funding opportunities.

Québec.name: Concordia University
Québec.description: Concordia is a next-generation university, continually reimagining the future of higher education. Established in 1974, Concordia is located in vibrant and multicultural Montreal, North America’s favourite student city. Its two campuses are situated in Tiohtià:ke/Montreal, on the traditional lands and waters of the Kanien’kehá:ka Nation. Concordia is the top-ranked university in North America under 50 and among the most innovative in its approach to experiential learning and cross-functional research.Concordia delivers on its commitment to the United Nations’ Sustainable Development Goals and is ranked fifth in the world for its promotion of Smart, Resilient Cities and Communities.The university strives to be socially responsible and impactful, aims to be forward-looking, agile and responsive while remaining deeply rooted in the community and globally networked. About 74 per cent of Concordia’s courses have fewer than 60 students. Its student body includes over 36,500 undergraduate students and 9,350 graduate students in more than 120 grad programs, nearly 10,000 international students from some 150 countries and 5,000-plus co-op students. Concordia maintains formal ties with more than 180 institutions in nearly 40 countries.For more information, visit Concordia.ca.

Québec.name: École de technologie supérieure
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. L’École de technologie supérieure (ÉTS) est une constituante du réseau de l’Université du Québec. Spécialisée dans l’enseignement et la recherche appliqués en génie et le transfert technologique, elle forme des ingénieurs et des chercheurs reconnus pour leur approche pratique et innovatrice.Par sa mission axée sur le génie appliqué et ses liens étroits avec l’industrie, l’ÉTS se distingue nettement des établissements universitaires québécois. Elle est de plus la seule école d’ingénierie au Québec qui offre des programmes de baccalauréat créés spécifiquement pour les diplômés de niveau collégial technique.L’ÉTS propose quelque 86 programmes d’études aux trois cycles – dont certains ne sont offerts nulle part ailleurs – et mise sur l’enseignement coopératif. Cette formule permet aux étudiants du baccalauréat et à certains des cycles supérieurs d’apprendre en pratiquant. Ils doivent réussir trois stages rémunérés en industrie, totalisant au moins douze mois, pour obtenir leur diplôme. L’École forme 25 pour cent de tous les ingénieurs québécois et propose des programmes de maîtrise et de doctorat dans de nombreux domaines du génie. Les programmes de l’ÉTS mènent directement, une fois le diplôme obtenu, à l’admission à l’Ordre des ingénieurs du Québec.

Québec.name: École nationale d’administration publique
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. L’École nationale d’administration publique (ENAP) est la seule université francophone spécialisée en administration publique en Amérique du Nord possédant une fine connaissance de la réalité des ministères et organismes gouvernementaux, des municipalités, du réseau de la santé et des services sociaux et du réseau de l’éducation. Elle dispose également d’une expertise des administrations publiques des pays de la Francophonie et, particulièrement, d’Europe, d’Afrique francophone et d’Haïti.L’ENAP offre 38 programmes de 2e et 3e cycles en présence, en mode hybride ou à distance. Plusieurs concentrations sont possibles :  administration et gestion internationales, développement des ressources humaines et des organisations, en gestion de la santé et des services sociaux, en évaluation de programmes, en gouvernance du numérique, etc.Ses programmes de 9 à 45 crédits offrent la possibilité de cheminer par étapes tandis que les cours sont offerts à temps plein ou à temps partiel, le jour, le soir et la fin de semaine afin d’offrir un maximum de nos clientèles, souvent déjà à l’emploi. Les programmes de l’ENAP sont conçus pour répondre aux besoins spécifiques des actrices et des acteurs des services publics afin qu’ils puissent relever les défis de l’avenir. Grâce à son personnel enseignant multidisciplinaires et la recherche de pointe qu’elle mène avec sa dizaine de regroupements de recherche dans des domaines touchant l’administration publique comme le numérique, le développement durable, la gestion de crise ou les gouvernements de proximité, les diplômées et diplômés de l’ENAP sont outillés peu importe leur trajectoire professionnelle.En raison de sa petite taille, une des grandes forces de l’ENAP est d’offrir des services personnalisés à sa clientèle étudiante afin d’accroître la réussite, soutenir la persévérance, et ce, dans un environnement sain et bienveillant.

Québec.name: HEC Montréal
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Founded in 1907, HEC Montréal is Canada’s first business school. It holds the three most prestigious international accreditations in its field, confirming the excellence of the training and support it offers: AACSB, EQUIS and AMBA. HEC Montréal has been designated as an Ashoka U Changemaker Campus, making it the world’s first French-language campus to receive this recognition. This designation salutes the school’s efforts to advance social innovation and changemaking across higher education.At the crossroads of two continents and countless cultures, HEC Montréal enjoys a privileged position within the French-speaking world and around the globe. The school gives its students a learning experience attuned to the globalized business community. HEC Montréal offers a Master of Science in Administration program with 25 specializations, as well as an MBA available on a full-time or part-time basis, and – in cooperation with McGill University – an Executive MBA program. Its PhD program is a joint program with three other Montreal universities, with 12 specializations. It brings together the latest thinking in management and research orientations from both Europe and North America.In addition, students can choose from 27 certificates, 20 specialized graduate diplomas, and a number of short graduate and undergraduate programs (micro programs). Moreover, HEC Montréal welcomes 3,676 international students from 145 countries.Research has expanded considerably at HEC Montréal over the past decade. It now boasts some 66 research chairs and transfer units, with more than $37,1 million in research funding.HEC Montréal is located on Mount Royal, just minutes away from two main metro stations. All urban amenities are conveniently located nearby.

Québec.name: Institut national de la recherche scientifique
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Fondé en 1969, l’Institut national de la recherche scientifique (INRS) est un établissement universitaire de recherche et de formation de deuxième et troisième cycles, qui rassemble 150 professeurs-chercheurs répartis dans quatre centres de recherche thématiques situés à Montréal, à Québec, à Laval et à Varennes. Elle accueille près de 800 étudiants et stagiaires postdoctoraux.Étudier à l’INRS, c’est travailler de concert dans l’équipe d’un professeur. Cette intégration immédiate, qui perdure jusqu’à la fin du programme d’études, assure le développement des connaissances et de savoir-faire, car les étudiants sont exposés à la dynamique de la recherche scientifique et prennent part aux activités de production et de diffusion qui en résultent. Ils bénéficient d’un encadrement personnalisé et apprennent à assumer toutes les tâches liées à l’exercice du métier de chercheur. L’INRS dispose de 15 chaires de recherche du Canada et sept autres chaires, en plus de posséder plusieurs infrastructures de recherche à la fine pointe de la technologie. Ses activités de recherche ont donné lieu à d’importantes avancées scientifiques, par exemple dans le domaine du cancer, des maladies infectieuses, de l’énergie durable, des technologies environnementales vertes et des applications technologiques en décontamination.

Québec.name: McGill University
Québec.description: Founded in 1821, McGill University attracts people inspired by challenge and committed to shaping a better future. McGill researchers are not only recognized for their scientific and technological breakthroughs, but also for examining the social, environmental, ethical and policy impacts of business practices, technology, science and medicine.  The diverse composition of McGill’s community, with approximately 50% of students from Quebec, 20% from the rest of Canada and 30% international, plus professors drawn from across the world, fosters an entrepreneurial and creative environment. Cutting-edge facilities, innovative teaching programs and multidisciplinary research attract first-class students and professors from all over the world. Top researchers regularly teach undergraduate classes and engage students in inquiry-based learning. Faculty and students participate in extensive research collaborations with the world’s best universities and institutions.McGill’s resources for learning and discovery include a vast array of research centres and networks, the Redpath Museum, branch libraries and special collections, research stations in the sub-Arctic and Arctic, and the Gault Nature Reserve.

Québec.name: Polytechnique Montréal
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Polytechnique Montréal est une université qui se spécialise dans la formation d’ingénieur(e)s et de chercheur(e)s en ingénierie et mathématiques de très haut niveau.Forte de ses 1 600 employé(e)s dont 300 professeur(e)s, l’institution offre des programmes aux trois cycles dans tous les domaines du génie. Arrimés aux grands enjeux socio-économiques, l’apprentissage valorise l’interdisciplinarité et le travail en équipe, et intègre les valeurs de développement durable. La formation de l’ingénieur inclut au moins un stage en entreprise obligatoire. Le développement d’un esprit entrepreneurial est une des priorités de l’établissement. Ainsi Polytechnique Montréal soutient une cinquantaine de comités et de sociétés gérés par les étudiant(e)s, et un parcours de formation de jeunes entrepreneurs. Polytechnique Montréal propose également de nombreuses opportunités d’échanges internationaux ainsi que des programmes de doubles diplômes, grâce à des ententes académiques avec de prestigieuses universités européennes et asiatiques.

Québec.name: Université de Montréal
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Fondée en 1878, l’Université de Montréal (UdeM) figure parmi les meilleures universités dans le monde.L’UdeM compte 13 facultés et écoles, deux grandes écoles affiliées – HEC Montréal et Polytechnique Montréal – ainsi qu’une trentaine d’établissements de santé affiliés. Plus de 67 000 personnes sont inscrites à ses quelque 250 programmes de premier cycle et 350 programmes de deuxième et troisième cycles. Le corps professoral de l’UdeM et de ses écoles affiliées regroupe 2 300 professeurs et chercheurs permanents et invités.Dans le domaine de la recherche, l’UdeM est reconnue comme l’une des cinq universités les plus dynamiques du Canada. Son campus abrite plus de 465 unités de recherche, dont 145 chaires de recherche du Canada, deux chaires d’excellence en recherche du Canada et une chaire de recherche Canada 150. Ses chercheurs et chercheuses recueillent, avec ses établissements affiliés, plus d’un demi-milliard de dollars en subventions de recherche chaque année. Situé sur le mont Royal, au cœur de Montréal, le campus de l’UdeM occupe un environnement exceptionnel, dont les deux tiers sont constitués d’espaces boisés. Trois stations de métro et plusieurs lignes d’autobus donnent directement accès au campus, qui surplombe un quartier cosmopolite bien fourni en restaurants, cafés, librairies et services de toutes sortes.

Québec.name: Université de Sherbrooke
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Fondée en 1954, l’Université de Sherbrooke est une université francophone située à 150 km de Montréal. Elle offre, aux trois cycles d’enseignement, près de 400 programmes dans lesquels elle accueille plus de  41 000 étudiantes et étudiants provenant de 96  pays et territoires.L’Université de Sherbrooke est composée de huit facultés (droit, école de gestion, éducation, génie, lettres et sciences humaines, médecine et sciences de la santé, sciences, sciences de l’activité physique) et de trois centres universitaires (études du religieux contemporain, enrichissement de la formation à la recherche, formation en environnement et développement durable). L’Université offre aussi son programme de médecine à Saguenay (Québec) et à Moncton (Nouveau-Brunswick) grâce aux partenariats avec l’Université du Québec à Chicoutimi et l’Université de Moncton.L’Université de Sherbrooke est une pionnière de l’enseignement coopératif. Elle est aujourd’hui considérée comme le chef de file de cette méthode qui permet à plusieurs étudiants d’ajouter à leurs connaissances théoriques une expérience pratique acquise en milieu de travail grâce aux stages rémunérés.La réputation d’excellence de l’Université de Sherbrooke s’appuie également sur ses activités de recherche qui ont conduit à des découvertes majeures. De nombreux transferts technologiques sont effectués vers les entreprises afin de favoriser la commercialisation de technologies compétitives.

Québec.name: Université du Québec
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Depuis plus de 50 ans, nous sommes l’Université du Québec. Un réseau collaboratif francophone reconnu pour son excellence, son accessibilité et son ouverture. Nous transformons les vies, les savoirs, le Québec et le monde tout en intégrant la diversité des réalités qui façonnent le Québec de l’est à l’ouest du sud au nord.Près de 100 000 étudiantes et étudiants fréquentent plus de 1 300 programmes offerts par l’un des dix établissements du réseau : l’Université du Québec à Montréal (UQAM), l’Université du Québec à Trois-Rivières (UQTR), l’Université du Québec à Chicoutimi (UQAC), l’Université du Québec à Rimouski (UQAR), l’Université du Québec en Outaouais (UQO), l’Université du Québec en Abitibi-Témiscamingue (UQAT), l’Institut national de la recherche scientifique (INRS), l’École nationale d’administration publique (ENAP), l’École de technologie supérieure (ÉTS) et l’Université TÉLUQ. Depuis sa fondation en 1968, l’Université du Québec a décerné plus de 750 000 diplômes.Ce sont plus de 7 000 professeurs/professeures et personnes chargées de cours et 4 500 membres du personnel régulier qui assurent au quotidien la mission universitaire d’enseignement et de recherche, dans une cinquantaine de villes et municipalités du Québec. En 2020-2021, les octrois de recherche obtenus par les établissements de l’Université du Québec totalisaient 295,3 millions de dollars. Ils comptent près de 500 groupes et laboratoires de recherche, dont 200 chaires de recherche.

Québec.name: Université du Québec à Chicoutimi (UQAC)
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Fondée en 1969, l’Université du Québec à Chicoutimi fait partie du plus grand réseau universitaire du Canada, celui de l’Université du Québec. Située au cœur du Saguenay−Lac-Saint-Jean, une région francophone reconnue pour la beauté de son fjord, elle déploie ses activités d’enseignement, de recherche et de création à travers son campus principal, ses centres d’études universitaires ainsi que son école du numérique. L’UQAC se distingue mondialement grâce à l’expertise de ses professeurs-chercheurs, à l’excellence de ses étudiants et à l’innovation dont elle fait preuve tant en enseignement qu’en recherche. Elle contribue, notamment par l’entremise de ses créneaux d’excellence, à l’avancement de la recherche et de la création et au rayonnement de sa communauté. Dans une société du savoir avide de créativité et de nouveauté, l’UQAC constitue plus que jamais un instrument essentiel à la transmission et à la diffusion des connaissances à l’échelle régionale, nationale et internationale.

Québec.name: Université du Québec à Montréal (UQAM)
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. L’Université du Québec à Montréal (UQAM) est une université francophone dont le rayonnement est international. Elle offre plus de 300 programmes d’études rattachés à son École des sciences de la gestion (ESG UQAM) ou à l’une ou l’autre de ses six facultés : arts, communication, science politique et droit, sciences, sciences de l’éducation et sciences humaines.Créée en 1969 pour faciliter l’accès aux études universitaires et démocratiser le savoir et la culture, l’UQAM déploie d’importants efforts en matière de recherche et de création, grâce à plus de 100 unités de recherche, dont plus de 80 chaires et 6 instituts. Très présente dans les secteurs des sciences humaines et des arts, l’Université cible également des créneaux prometteurs en sciences naturelles et de la santé. Le campus central et le Complexe des sciences Pierre-Dansereau prennent place au cœur des deux quartiers les plus animés de Montréal : le Quartier latin et le Quartier des spectacles. L’UQAM reçoit aussi des étudiants dans ses quatre campus situés dans les régions de Lanaudière, de Laval, de Longueuil et de la Montérégie-Ouest. Elle accueille près de 40 000 étudiants, dont plus de 8 000 aux cycles supérieurs et plus de 4 300 étudiants étrangers provenant de 95 pays.

Québec.name: Université du Québec à Rimouski (UQAR)
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. L’UQAR accueille annuellement environ 6700 étudiantes et étudiants, dont plus de 650 venant d’une quarantaine de pays. En plus de ses deux campus situés sur la rive sud du fleuve Saint-Laurent à Rimouski et à Lévis, l’UQAR offre de la formation universitaire à la grandeur de l’Est-du-Québec.L’UQAR est reconnue pour l’encadrement exceptionnel de son corps professoral et des personnes chargées de cours. Les classes comptent une moyenne de 30 étudiantes et étudiants, ce qui facilite l’intégration et la réussite des études.Tout en mettant l’accent sur la réussite étudiante, les programmes de formation offerts à l’UQAR se distinguent par leur excellence et par leur caractère unique. Avec sa situation géographique privilégiée, l’UQAR permet aux étudiantes et aux étudiants d’explorer et d’étudier des milieux naturels exceptionnels à deux pas des campus. De nombreux programmes comprennent une forte proportion de travaux pratiques sur le terrain ou des stages en milieu de travail. Riche de la grande diversité de ses expertises de calibre international, l’UQAR se démarque parmi les universités les plus dynamiques en recherche au Canada. Année après année, l’UQAR se classe parmi les meilleures universités canadiennes en recherche. Depuis 2011, l’Université s’est classée à neuf reprises dans les trois premiers rangs du palmarès de la firme Research Infosource, dans la catégorie des universités offrant majoritairement des programmes de 1er cycle.

Québec.name: Université du Québec à Trois-Rivières (UQTR)
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Créée en 1969 et membre du réseau de l’Université du Québec, l’Université du Québec à Trois-Rivières (UQTR) a formé plus de 86 000 diplômés et accueille annuellement environ 15 000 étudiants aux trois cycles d’études dans près de 340 programmes, dont plusieurs uniques au Québec.Avec des stages dans la majorité des programmes de premier cycle, des projets d’intervention communautaire et plus de 100 cours en ligne, l’UQTR se déploie à l’extérieur du campus trifluvien avec des campus à Drummondville, à L’Assomption et à Québec et six centres universitaires répartis dans la province. L’UQTR a développé une expertise d’envergure internationale dans plusieurs domaines favorisant l’avancement des connaissances fondamentales et appliquées. Les étudiants peuvent bonifier leur formation auprès de chercheurs renommés dans les thématiques de recherche telles que 1) l’environnement et les transitions énergétiques; 2) les innovations technologiques, sociales et culturelles; 3) les savoirs fondamentaux et cliniques en santé humaine; et 4) Société et santé inclusives.L’UQTR se distingue par une vie universitaire et régionale dynamiques, des programmes originaux, des projets de recherche novateurs, mais surtout par son accueil chaleureux et la dimension enviable de son campus. En somme, l’UQTR est une grande université de taille humaine.

Québec.name: Université du Québec en Abitibi-Témiscamingue (UQAT)
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Humaine, créative, audacieuse, l’Université du Québec en Abitibi-Témiscamingue (UQAT) est une université francophone qui compte près de 7 000 étudiantes et étudiants, dont 400 provenant de l’étranger. Membre du réseau de l’Université du Québec, elle démontre depuis 1970 un incomparable dynamisme dans les domaines de l’enseignement et de la recherche.Université au Québec couvrant le plus grand territoire, elle offre des programmes dans ses campus, centres et point de service en Abitibi-Témiscamingue, dans le Nord-du-Québec, les Hautes-Laurentides et Montréal. Pour remplir adéquatement sa mission, elle s’est dotée des technologies de pointe en enseignement à distance.L’UQAT offre plus de 175 programmes de premier, deuxième et troisième cycles dans plusieurs domaines d’études : agriculture, création numérique, 3D et jeux vidéo, art-thérapie, études autochtones, développement humain,  travail social, éducation, forêts, génie, gestion, mines, eaux souterraines et environnement ainsi que santé. Divers programmes sont également offerts aux Premiers Peuples, dont certains en anglais. Véritable laboratoire à ciel ouvert, l’université est un milieu unique de recherche qui affiche une très haute performance en recherche. La proximité avec le terrain ainsi que les nombreux partenariats établis avec le milieu offrent des expériences de recherche concrètes. L’UQAT se classe parmi les 3 universités canadiennes principalement actives au 1er cycle les plus performantes en recherche selon le palmarès 2021 de la firme RE$EARCH Infosource. L’UQAT se distingue avantageusement dans plusieurs secteurs : acceptabilité sociale, agroalimentaire, bioproduits, communications souterraines, développement des petites collectivités, écologie et aménagement forestier durable, entrepreneuriat minier, questions autochtones, hydrogéologie, ingénierie, restauration des sites miniers, abandonnés, sylviculture et ligniculture intensive ainsi que valorisation et transformation du bois.

Québec.name: Université du Québec en Outaouais
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. L’Université du Québec en Outaouais (UQO) est reconnue pour sa dimension humaine qui facilite l’apprentissage et la réflexion. La grande disponibilité du personnel enseignant permet un excellent encadrement et une relation privilégiée entre étudiants et professeurs.Située à Gatineau, au cœur de l’Outaouais, l’UQO est logée dans deux pavillons à distance de marche l’un de l’autre et jouit d’un avantage géographique et culturel certain. Elle a en effet l’avantage d’être située dans une zone frontalière marquée par la riche présence de deux cultures qui vivent au rythme des activités fébriles de la capitale fédérale, Ottawa. Non seulement présente en milieu urbain, l’UQO offre également des services en périphérie et travaille dans le but d’accroître sa présence en région au cours des années à venir.Depuis 2010, l’UQO se retrouve également à Saint-Jérôme dans un nouvel immeuble de 10 132 mètres carrés, construit à l’angle des rues Saint-Joseph et Labelle, face à la mairie. Ce campus accueille plus de 2 500 étudiants et étudiantes. On trouve des salles de classe, des laboratoires d’enseignement et de recherche, une bibliothèque, une didacthèque, des aires de rencontre pour les étudiants et étudiantes, des bureaux, des espaces administratifs, et des services auxiliaires, tels qu’une cafétéria et une librairie, répartis sur les six étages. L’UQO offre des programmes de premier cycle et de cycles supérieurs à plus de 7 000 étudiants dans les disciplines suivantes : administration, arts et patrimoines, éducation, ingénierie, informatique, psychoéducation, psychologie, relations industrielles et ressources humaines, sciences comptables, sciences naturelles, sciences sociales, sciences infirmières, traduction et rédaction ainsi que travail social.L’UQO est d’ailleurs la seule université québécoise à offrir en français le baccalauréat en relations industrielles et en ressources humaines (cheminement coopératif), des programmes de premier cycle en muséologie et patrimoines ainsi qu’en bande dessinée, le doctorat en sciences de la famille et le doctorat en sciences sociales appliquées.Grâce à ses nombreux groupes de recherche, l’UQO contribue au développement scientifique, notamment par ses onzechaires de recherche et par son Institut des sciences de la forêt tempérée (ISFORT), situé à Ripon, qui est le premier institut au Canada dédié à l’étude de la forêt tempérée feuillue.

Québec.name: Université Laval
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Fondée en 1852, l’Université Laval se classe parmi les plus grandes universités canadiennes. Elle compte quelque 47 000 étudiantes et étudiants, 1 650 professeures et professeurs ainsi que 2 265 membres du personnel enseignant et de recherche, qui sont répartis dans 17 facultés et plus de 60 départements, écoles et instituts. Elle constitue une université de prestige à dimension humaine, implantée sur un campus vert et boisé, au cœur de la ville de Québec.La choisir, c’est bâtir son avenir dans un milieu de vie exceptionnel, où tout est mis en œuvre pour faciliter la réussite: un choix de programme parmi plus de 550 offerts aux trois cycles d’études; des séjours et des stages à l’étranger financés; une qualité d’encadrement reconnue; une vie culturelle, sportive et sociale très animée. Plus de 90 pour cent des programmes de premier cycle comprennent des stages obligatoires ou optionnels, sans compter les profils d’études offerts: international, entrepreneurial, développement durable, distinction et recherche. L’Université est aussi réputée pour ses programmes de stages et de séjours d’études à l’étranger, en plus d’offrir des cours de langue pour s’y préparer.

Québec.name: Université TÉLUQ
Québec.description: The following description is provided by the institution in the working language at that institution. Créée en 1972 et composante du réseau de l’Université du Québec, l’Université TÉLUQ est le seul établissement d’enseignement universitaire francophone en Amérique du Nord qui se consacre à la formation à distance. Pionnière et leader de ce mode de formation, elle offre plus de 125 programmes et 430 cours aux premier, deuxième et troisième cycles. Par son accessibilité au savoir, l’Université TÉLUQ permet chaque année à quelque 20 000 étudiants de conjuguer les études universitaires avec leurs projets personnels et professionnels.Accessible de partout dans le monde, l’Université TÉLUQ est membre du réseau de l’Université du Québec, le plus vaste réseau universitaire au Canada. Elle déploie ses activités d’enseignement dans les principaux domaines du savoir, dont l’administration, la comptabilité et les finances, la psychologie, les technologies éducatives, les technologies de l’information et la gouvernance des technologies, ainsi que les sciences humaines et sociales.Avec la formation à distance, l’Université TÉLUQ permet aux étudiants de limiter leurs déplacements et d’organiser leur horaire selon leurs besoins. Ainsi, ils concilient plus aisément travail, études et vie personnelle. Tout au long de leur parcours, ils bénéficient d’un soutien et d’un encadrement personnalisés. Parmi les autres grands secteurs de recherche de l’Université TÉLUQ, on trouve : l’informatique cognitive, l’économie du savoir, l’articulation emploi-famille, la psychologie sociale, l’environnement et la santé mentale.

Saskatchewan.name: Campion College
Saskatchewan.description: As Canada’s only Jesuit undergraduate college and a federated partner of the University of Regina, Campion offers students the opportunity to pursue their U of R degree as part of the bigger campus while taking advantage of the personalized service and support of a community-within-a-community. It is also part of the International Association of Jesuit Universities (IAJU) which includes over 190 member institutions worldwide.Any University of Regina student enrolled in the Faculties of Arts; Science; or Media, Art, and Performance can enroll through Campion, including flexible options for those in pre-professional programs. Campion is committed to developing students as a whole to create leaders who truly believe in giving back to their communities by uniting academic excellence with a focus on ethical values and service to others, regardless of their religious affiliation or cultural background. The goal is for students to graduate with a desire to make the world a better place for all.Campion has award-winning professors are recognized for their research, academic achievements, and expertise in their field. Programs are designed to help students develop analytical, research, and communication skills while also encouraging students to engage and give back to others. The top reasons our students come – and stay – at Campion is the excellent, personalized one-on-one academic advising and over $150,000 in scholarship and bursaries in addition to those offered by the University of Regina.Come to Campion College at the University of Regina where it’s an education for the whole you and you’ll discover who you’re meant to be.

Saskatchewan.name: First Nations University of Canada
Saskatchewan.description: The First Nations University of Canada, established in 1976, is the first FirstNations-controlled university in Canada and a leader in Indigenous-based education.The First Nations University of Canada incorporates Indigenous worldviews and knowledge into all aspects of the university. It aims to give First Nations, Métis, and other Indigenous learners the most significant opportunity to succeed in their education and, in turn, to strengthen their communities through their accomplishments.The First Nations University of Canada is open to students of all backgrounds and is committed to inclusivity and respect for people of all cultures. Each year, thousands of non-Indigenous students attend its classes. For many, this allows them to prepare to work in their chosen fields while helping them network and build relationships with Indigenous people. At FNUniv, we have partnered with the University of Regina, Faculty of Graduate Studies &Research to offer three Indigenous focused-graduate programs to further one’s studies in Education, Language, and Social Work.Students learn through traditional oral teachings, through Elders in the classrooms and by participating in traditional ceremonies. Students can access its range of programs at its three Saskatchewan campuses in Regina, Saskatoon, and Prince Albert. The university also offers web-based courses, distance education, and community-based programs. These flexible learning environments give students the quality education they seek and the convenience of taking their degree from locations near or within their home communities. For many, this allows connection to family and community while also providing quality education.At the First Nations University of Canada, we are family. We are unique. We are home. We are Indigenous!

Saskatchewan.name: Luther College
Saskatchewan.description: Luther College is a liberal arts and sciences college federated with the University of Regina. Located on the beautiful University of Regina (U of R) campus, Luther offers degrees in the Arts; Sciences; Media, Art, and Performance; and an array of excellent pre-professional options. Here, students have all the benefits of a larger campus without feeling lost in the crowd. Luther students are U of R students, pay the same tuition and fees, and receive a U of R degree. Luther students take classes across campus, and access all the U of R services, but also get the extra services reserved especially for Luther College students. We are recognized for high standards of teaching, focused research, and student support.Luther’s academic advisors and enrollment counsellors work closely with students to navigate through their university journey. Our faculty encourage students to explore, learn, and transform passion into a meaningful career. Students receive one-on-one academic advising throughout their time at Luther. The College is known for making the transition from high school to university easy. Designed to give students a successful start to university, optional groups of courses, called Bundles, can be chosen when registering for first semester.We are rooted in the Lutheran heritage and intellectual tradition, and we honour the beliefs of those we serve, those with and without faith traditions. We appeal to all students who want to study in a nurturing and inclusive academic environment! The Student Village residence at Luther College is also a great choice for first-year accommodation! Our all-inclusive atmosphere lets students add responsibility slowly, so they can focus on studying, making friends, and their overall wellness. All rooms have been completely renovated and come with a meal plan, free laundry, free Wi-Fi, and a great sense of community.

Saskatchewan.name: St. Thomas More College
Saskatchewan.description: Located in Saskatoon, St. Thomas More College (STM) is a Catholic liberal arts college federated with the University of Saskatchewan (USask), open to all students. By providing students with an intimate scholarly setting within the USask campus, STM students are given access to the best of both worlds.Founded by the Basilian Fathers in 1936, and now under the sponsorship of the St. Thomas More College Society, STM is a welcoming community recognized for strong traditions of academic excellence, passion for social justice and fostering student growth as whole persons.STM is academically integrated with USask and, in partnership with the College of Arts and Science, offers over 250 credit classes in 19 subject areas. Any student may take STM courses as part of their USask degree. Over 5,000 students register in courses offered through STM with course credit counted toward the requirements of Arts and Science degrees, and in many cases, fulfilling the elective requirements in other USask degree programs. STM also offers students opportunities to incorporate community service-learning into their academic experience.Recognized for its successful drama and glee club, several youth groups, a student governing body within the college, STM additionally supports students through academic advising and an on-site campus ministry team.

Saskatchewan.name: University of Regina
Saskatchewan.description: The University of Regina is a comprehensive, mid-sized university that traces its roots back to the creation of Regina College in 1911. The College grew in size and significance and became an independent degree-granting university – the University of Regina – in 1974. Home to 10 faculties, 25 academic departments and schools, 18 research centres and institutes, and three federated colleges — Campion College, First Nations University of Canada, and Luther College — the university has  established reputations for excellence and innovative programs leading to bachelor’s, master’s and doctoral degrees.The University offers more than 120 undergraduate programs and 78 graduate programs, including many specialized programs such as police studies and public policy. Our commitment to discovery and opportunity extends beyond our campus and also finds its meaning in research undertaken through community and international partnerships. Through the University’s 2020-2025 Strategic Plan, All our Relations — kahkiyaw kiwâhkômâkaninawak — the U of R is committed to five areas of focus and the specific goals related to each: Discovery; Truth and Reconciliation; Well-being and Belonging; Environment and Climate Action; and Impact and Identity.U of R’s campuses in Regina and Saskatoon are located on Treaty 4 and Treaty 6 territories and the traditional homelands of the Métis. In Regina, the main campus and the historic College Avenue Campus utilize 239 acres and provide an attractive study and work environment for its students, faculty and staff. Both Regina campuses are located in Wascana Centre, one of the largest urban parks in North America.

Saskatchewan.name: University of Saskatchewan
Saskatchewan.description: The University of Saskatchewan (USask) is one of Canada’s most distinguished universities. Established in 1907, USask is a member of the U15 Group of Canadian research-intensive universities, and is known for its collaborative, interdisciplinary approaches to tackling some of the greatest global challenges of our era — vaccine development and infectious diseases, water and food security, energy sustainability and more.More than 26,000 students from 130 countries study in over 150 undergraduate and graduate programs spanning from business to medicine to engineering. USask offers more than $28.5 million in student scholarships and awards every year, and students enjoy a high level of support typical of a smaller university in a thriving environment that inspires collaboration, innovation and discovery. USask’s more than 169,000 living alumni are spread across the world. Our graduates, recognized for their work ethic, resourcefulness and determination, will continue to build on a long history of success to address the world’s challenges now and in the future.
